Package: adjROC
Type: Package
Title: Computes Adjusted Sensitivity, Adjusted Specificity, or the Crossing Point Between Sensitivity and Specificity
Version: 0.1.0
Author: E. F. Haghish
Maintainer: E. F. Haghish <haghish@uio.no>
Description: For a binary classification the adjusted sensitivity and specificity are measured for a given fixed threshold. If the threshold for either sensitivity or sensitivity is not given, the crossing point between the sensitivity and specificity curves are returned.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: ROCit, ggplot2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Improved confidence intervals for the sensitivity at a fixed level of specificity of a continuous-scale diagnostic test
